    {
      "id": "2035257217080074459",
      "text": "I had dinner once with a top physicist and a top computer scientist and asked what they thought the probability was that we were in a simulation. \n\nThey answered simultaneously at 0% and 100% respectively. It was like a double-slit experiment, but with humans.",
      "created_at": "Sat Mar 21 07:28:28 +0000 2026",
      "lang": "en",
      "media": [],
      "retweet": null,
      "quoted": {
        "id": "2035014752074965316",
        "text": "🚨 Simulation Theory:  The Double Slit Experiment proves particles act like waves until observed then they snap into particles. \n\nWhat if our reality only \"renders\" when we're looking, just like a video game optimizing resources?  \n\nCheck out this episode from The Why Files breaking it down, tying it to Simulation Theory. Are we in a sim? \n\nThis could be the key to unlocking the true nature of existence!   \n\nThe Why Files video did a great job on explaining the Double Slit Experiment & Simulation Theory   \n\nWhat do YOU think—real or rendered? Drop your thoughts below!",
        "created_at": "Fri Mar 20 15:25:00 +0000 2026",
        "lang": "en",
        "media": [
          {
